        "description": "EMUNI University was established on 9 June 2008 in Portorož, Slovenia, with the objective of becoming an international, post-graduate, higher-education and research institution, fully integrated in the Euro-Mediterranean Area. It was co-founded by four universities: University of Haifa (Israel), University of Maribor (Slovenia), University of Sousse (Tunisia) and University of Urbino \"Carlo Bo\" (Italy). In February 2009 EMUNI University became a legal entity in the Republic of Slovenia."
